02:19:52,855 --> 02:19:56,685
You're right. But didn't
your son die last year?

1365
02:19:57,268 --> 02:20:01,514
"Kavita, you lost your sister."
"And Mrs. Khanna, you lost your father."

1366
02:20:02,138 --> 02:20:06,388
But you've all dressed up to the do.
- The rules for a widow are different

1367
02:20:07,507 --> 02:20:09,879
That's our culture.

1368
02:20:09,880 --> 02:20:13,880
Rules? Dual standards! If you lose
"a father, son, or brother..."

1369
02:20:17,123 --> 02:20:20,495
you don't grieve. But if you lose
a husband you should wear white.

1370
02:20:21,077 --> 02:20:25,489
"Why? I ask, why are these rules"
"only for women, and not for men?"

1371
02:20:26,154 --> 02:20:29,899
Why don't widowers
wear white dresses?

1372
02:20:29,899 --> 02:20:33,145
Great are the traditions of my
country. If that's how things are...

1373
02:20:33,148 --> 02:20:37,436
Kajal will soon cease to be a widow.
We'll get her married again.

1374
02:20:40,558 --> 02:20:43,802
"Monty, come with me."

1375
02:20:43,802 --> 02:20:47,217
Put the engagements rings
on each other.

1376
02:20:47,217 --> 02:20:50,423
"What are you doing, Jiya?"
You and Raj are going to be engaged.

1377
02:20:50,423 --> 02:20:53,586
"Sure, but first the elder daughter"
"should be engaged, right Papa?"

1378
02:20:54,254 --> 02:20:59,120
"Of course. Kajal, we consider you"
"our daughter, not a daughter-in-law."

1379
02:20:59,952 --> 02:21:03,077
And we took a decision
in the best of your interests.

1380
02:21:03,619 --> 02:21:07,197
"Yes my child, you have"
a whole life ahead of you.

1381
02:21:07,197 --> 02:21:10,529
And we're thankful to Mr. Singhaniya
for his noble thought.

1382
02:21:10,986 --> 02:21:16,645
What are you saying? Did anyone
ask me if I'm willing to marry?

1383
02:21:17,188 --> 02:21:20,101
"Bhabhi, does Monty lack something?"
- Jiya!

1384
02:21:20,101 --> 02:21:23,096
Or are you in love with someone else?
- What nonsense!

1385
02:21:23,096 --> 02:21:29,596
It's the truth!
"You're in love with my fiancé, Raj."

1386
02:21:31,757 --> 02:21:33,629
"Enough Jiya, please!"
"- It's true, Kajal."

1387
02:21:33,630 --> 02:21:37,042
May I ask you what right you had
to threaten Raj with suicide...

1388
02:21:37,043 --> 02:21:41,120
"if he didn't marry me? Tell me,"
why did Raj agree to marry me?

1389
02:21:43,245 --> 02:21:45,572
"I know everything,"
I've heard everything.

1390
02:21:45,576 --> 02:21:48,947
It isn't acceptable to me that he
weds me and continues to love you.

1391
02:21:49,572 --> 02:21:52,942
"Stop it, Jaya!"
There's nothing of the sort.

1392
02:21:52,943 --> 02:21:56,230
"Look, if you wish, I'm ready"
for this marriage.

1393
02:21:56,230 --> 02:22:02,645
"Monty, come on,"
put the ring on my finger.

1394
02:22:11,218 --> 02:22:15,923
Stop!

1395
02:22:17,336 --> 02:22:20,248
"Come to your senses, Kajal."
You can't ruin your life...

1396
02:22:20,250 --> 02:22:23,327
for somebody else's happiness.
- Why? Why?

1397
02:22:23,327 --> 02:22:26,827
Does marrying again ruin one's life?
Why are you stopping her from marrying?

1398
02:22:27,326 --> 02:22:30,654
What does she mean to you? What
relationship do you share with her?

1399
02:22:30,654 --> 02:22:36,654
Do you want a wife and a mistress
together...?

1400
02:22:37,191 --> 02:22:43,190
Do you wish to know what
she means to me? Do you?

1401
02:23:25,727 --> 02:23:29,304
That's what she means to me.
She is my wife.

1402
02:23:29,306 --> 02:23:33,468
Any objections?

1403
02:23:33,468 --> 02:23:37,297
"Want to say something, aunt?"

1404
02:23:37,298 --> 02:23:40,335
Tell me!
- Raj....

1405
02:23:40,336 --> 02:23:43,414
it's just what I wanted. 

1406
02:23:43,414 --> 02:23:46,992
I staged this mock engagement
with Monty...

1407
02:23:46,996 --> 02:23:50,576
so that you would openly declare
your love for her.

1408
02:23:53,449 --> 02:23:56,904
"Not a burden, I want"
to become your wings...

1409
02:23:57,443 --> 02:24:03,442
"so that you can fly high,"
very high.

1410
02:24:03,685 --> 02:24:08,346
Jiya...

1411
02:24:08,347 --> 02:24:12,760
"you're grown up, really."

1412
02:24:12,760 --> 02:24:16,093
"I was mistaken about you, really."

1413
02:24:18,632 --> 02:24:22,000
"I ought to apologize to you, Raj."

1414
02:24:22,001 --> 02:24:26,664
"Though involuntarily,"
I have hurt Kajal no end.

1415
02:24:28,414 --> 02:24:33,827
"Forgive me, Kajal."

1416
02:24:41,855 --> 02:24:45,184
These traps of traditions...g

1417
02:24:45,185 --> 02:24:48,391
these shackles of promises...t

1418
02:24:48,393 --> 02:24:53,016
I could never break
even if I wish to

1419
02:24:54,760 --> 02:24:57,882
What kind of helplessness is this?

1420
02:24:57,884 --> 02:25:01,336
What kind of a life is this?

1421
02:25:01,336 --> 02:25:05,915
I could never break free
from old ties

1422
02:25:07,208 --> 02:25:12,327
"This is what life is all about,"
it is said

1423
02:25:16,154 --> 02:25:18,568
If you love someone...

1424
02:25:18,568 --> 02:25:21,525
express it...

1425
02:25:21,527 --> 02:25:26,770
before it is too late

1426
02:25:27,435 --> 02:25:30,391
If you trust someone...

1427
02:25:30,393 --> 02:25:33,011
say it... 

1428
02:25:33,015 --> 02:25:38,385
before it is too late.

1429
02:25:39,798 --> 02:25:44,711
That's the secret to steal hearts.

